All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
AggregationShape
Represents an aggregation relationship between two classes in a class diagram.
AssociationShape
Represents an association relationship between two shapes in a class diagram.
ClassShape
The ClassShape class represents a shape used to depict a class or interface in a UML-like diagram.
CodeGenerator
The CodeGenerator class is responsible for generating Java code for UML class diagrams represented by ClassShape.
CodeViewController
The CodeViewController class manages the user interface interactions related to displaying, copying, saving, and closing code files.
CompositionShape
Represents a composition relationship between two class shapes.
DAO
The DAO class is responsible for handling data access operations.
DependencyLineShape
Represents a dependency line between two shapes, used in class diagrams to indicate relationships.
Diagrams
This class represents a collection of diagram shapes and contains methods to manipulate, add attributes, methods, and delete shapes from the diagram.
DirectAssociationLineShape
Represents a direct association relationship between two class shapes.
GeneralizationShape
The GeneralizationShape class represents a generalization (inheritance or implementation) relationship between two class shapes.
ModelExplorer
ModelExplorer class is responsible for managing and updating the visual representation of the UML model in a TreeView.
Project
Project class to handle project-related operations like exporting to PNG.
ProjectManager
ProjectManager class responsible for managing projects, including saving, loading, and retrieving project names.
Shape
The Shape class serves as an abstract base class for all shapes in the application.
UMLEditorApp
The main application class for the UML Editor.
UseCaseShape
The UseCaseShape class represents a use-case oval shape that can be drawn on a canvas.
UserShape
The UserShape class represents a user-shaped stick figure that can be drawn on a canvas.
